STOP
QUESTION 4 
(a) Purpose
     fork() – Creates a child process.
     exec() – Replaces the current process with a new program.
(b) Role of wait()
     Waits for the child process to finish before the parent continues.
(c) Short Pseudo-code
START
pid = fork()
IF pid == 0
    exec("program")
ELSE
    wait()
END IF
STOP
